---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE, GAME } from '../consts';

const faq = [
  { q: 'How do you learn spells in Moonlight Peaks?', a: "Confirmed at launch: your wand starts broken. After the Dinner Party event, Luna sends a letter asking you to visit her farm; she gives you magical seeds to nurture, then points you to Sabrina — though it's actually Noel who fixes the wand, with duct tape. After that, spellcasting opens up." },
  { q: 'What spells are confirmed?', a: "Confirmed at launch: Aquaflux (a self-pouring watering spell, required for magical crops), maturing crops faster, clearing rocks, summoning rain, and a Witches' Circle teleport spell. You cast by drawing a circle-and-dot pattern with the wand equipped, and spells cost mana." },
  { q: 'What does the Alter Ego Elixir do?', a: 'The Alter Ego Elixir is a potion, sold by Sabrina at Web of Wonders, that changes your appearance. It is one example of the many brews you can make through potion-making.' },
  { q: 'Is magic required to play?', a: 'Witchcraft is a core pillar of the game and makes farming and gathering easier, but Moonlight Peaks is a cozy life sim — you can play at your own pace.' },
];

const jsonLd = [
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: faq.map((f) => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: f.q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a } })) },
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: SITE.url },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Magic', item: new URL('/magic', SITE.url).href },
  ] },
];
---
<Base
  title="Moonlight Peaks Magic — Spells, Potions & Elixirs"
  description="How magic works in Moonlight Peaks: learning spells from town witches, brewing potions like the Alter Ego Elixir, and how witchcraft helps farming and foraging."
  path="/magic"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Magic' }]}
  showExport
>
  <article class="page">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Entry · Magic</p>
      <h1>Moonlight Peaks <em>magic</em> — spells & potions</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        Witchcraft is one of the core pillars of {GAME.title}. Here's how spellcasting and
        potion-making work, and how they help your cozy vampire life. Updated {SITE.updated}.
      </p>

      <h2>Unlocking magic — confirmed quest chain</h2>
      <p>
        Confirmed at launch: your wand doesn't work at first. After the Dinner Party event, you get
        a letter on waking from Luna asking you to come to her farm. She gives you magical seeds to
        nurture, then — seeing your broken wand — points you toward Sabrina. Confirmed comedic twist:
        it's actually Noel who ends up fixing it, with duct tape. Once that's done, spellcasting opens up.
      </p>

      <h2>How casting works</h2>
      <p>
        Confirmed at launch: equip your wand, then draw a circle-and-dot pattern, following the
        on-screen prompt with the D-pad (or your Joy-Con/mouse). Below your stamina bar you'll see a
        separate mana bar — you start with a small pool and regain one star per night's sleep, so
        managing mana across a night matters. A few rare foods and drinks restore mana early on.
      </p>

      <h2>Confirmed spell list</h2>
      <p>
        Confirmed spells taught by the town's witches: <strong>Aquaflux</strong>, a self-pouring
        watering can spell unlocked from Luna after the Dinner Party quest chain (regular watering
        cans don't work on magical crops — they need Aquaflux); plus <strong>maturing crops</strong>
        faster, <strong>clearing rocks</strong>, <strong>summoning rain</strong>, and a
        <strong>Witches' Circle teleport</strong>. As you learn, you expand your repertoire further.
      </p>

      <h2>Potions & the Alter Ego Elixir</h2>
      <p>
        Alongside spells, you brew potions to unlock all kinds of effects. The headline example is
        the <strong>Alter Ego Elixir</strong>, sold by Sabrina at Web of Wonders, which changes your
        appearance. Potion-making is described as a key skill, so expect a range of brews with
        different uses across the game.
      </p>

      <h2>Witchcraft & your vampire powers</h2>
      <p>
        Magic sits alongside your vampire abilities — including <a href="/shapeshifting">shapeshifting
        into a bat or your Hellkitten</a>. See the
        <a href="/beginner-guide">beginner guide</a> for how the supernatural side fits together.
      </p>

      <h2>Coming at launch ({GAME.releaseLabel})</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The full <strong>spell list</strong> with what each does and how to unlock it.</li>
        <li>Every <strong>potion recipe</strong>, its ingredients, and its effect.</li>
        <li>Which witches teach what, and the best early spells to prioritise.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        {faq.map((f) => (
          <details>
            <summary>{f.q}</summary>
            <p>{f.a}</p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="callout wip">
        Pre-launch entry — spell and potion data lands at launch. Related:
        <a href="/farming">farming & crops</a>, <a href="/character-creator">character creator</a>, <a href="/shapeshifting">shapeshifting</a>, <a href="/items">items</a>, <a href="/beginner-guide">beginner guide</a>.
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
